1
00:00:14,633 --> 00:00:16,733
I accept your relationship
wholeheartedly.

2
00:00:16,800 --> 00:00:20,400
Only to find out you're
looking for your mom,

3
00:00:20,467 --> 00:00:23,333
who hates you and doesn't
care about you.

4
00:00:23,400 --> 00:00:25,033
It's so unfair.

5
00:00:25,700 --> 00:00:26,800
I'm sorry.

6
00:00:26,867 --> 00:00:28,267
No one died here.

7
00:00:28,333 --> 00:00:29,800
Sir, please receive the package.

8
00:00:30,033 --> 00:00:32,000
We're not going to
take that package!

9
00:00:32,067 --> 00:00:34,033
This is so annoying!

10
00:00:34,133 --> 00:00:36,967
They said they didn't
know the senders' address.

11
00:00:37,033 --> 00:00:38,433
But it came with a necklace.

12
00:00:38,500 --> 00:00:40,467
It's so obvious that
Amanda sent that!

13
00:00:40,533 --> 00:00:43,300
I thought my business
rival was Mr. Akashi.

14
00:00:43,367 --> 00:00:45,900
But he's just a financier.

15
00:00:45,967 --> 00:00:48,600
Rina and Zandro are his people.

16
00:00:48,667 --> 00:00:52,400
So you're helping me because you
want to bring them down.

17
00:00:52,467 --> 00:00:54,700
And because I still love you.

18
00:00:55,267 --> 00:00:56,267
Hello?

19
00:00:56,567 --> 00:00:58,000
I will kill you.

20
00:00:58,067 --> 00:01:00,300
I will kill all of you.

21
00:01:00,367 --> 00:01:02,067
Who is this?

22
00:01:02,133 --> 00:01:04,233
I will kill you first, monster!

23
00:01:04,300 --> 00:01:05,800
Stop it, no!

24
00:01:05,867 --> 00:01:07,000
Rina, Rina!

25
00:01:07,100 --> 00:01:08,467
- What's wrong?
- My God!

26
00:01:08,533 --> 00:01:10,933
The other day someone sent you
a funeral flower.

27
00:01:11,000 --> 00:01:11,967
And now, a death threat.

28
00:01:12,033 --> 00:01:13,533
I think this is serious.

29
00:01:13,600 --> 00:01:17,667
And I'm so sure that only
one person can do this.

30
00:01:17,733 --> 00:01:18,767
I'm sure it's Amanda!

31
00:01:18,833 --> 00:01:19,967
Amanda's behind all of this!

32
00:01:20,033 --> 00:01:22,767
She's the only person
who hates our family.

33
00:01:22,833 --> 00:01:25,000
Auntie, it could be
someone else.

34
00:01:25,067 --> 00:01:29,133
Well, she sent you, her
daughter, a funeral flower.

35
00:01:29,200 --> 00:01:30,533
Imagine what she'll do to me.

36
00:01:30,600 --> 00:01:33,500
She blames me for getting
separated from you.

37
00:01:33,567 --> 00:01:34,833
What's up, Rina?

38
00:01:34,900 --> 00:01:39,700
They believe that Amanda's
behind all the death threats.

39
00:01:40,233 --> 00:01:44,700
I'll play with you first
before I take you down.

40
00:01:44,800 --> 00:01:50,033
You will taste your
own medicine.

41
00:01:50,100 --> 00:01:53,733
You will feel every
inch of my wrath.

42
00:01:58,100 --> 00:02:01,000
Rina, aren't you worried that
Eden might lose the baby?

43
00:02:01,567 --> 00:02:02,733
What the hell do I care?

44
00:02:02,800 --> 00:02:04,933
I wish she had a miscarriage

45
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:06,867
when we sent her
the funeral flower.

46
00:02:08,900 --> 00:02:12,800
We're going to send Eden
a funeral flower.

47
00:02:12,867 --> 00:02:15,133
We'll make it look like
it came from her mom.

48
00:02:15,233 --> 00:02:18,700
Let's see how she'll react.

49
00:02:19,467 --> 00:02:21,900
I don't think she'll believe
it's from her mom.

50
00:02:22,567 --> 00:02:23,667
Amanda is still her mom.

51
00:02:24,133 --> 00:02:25,267
Give me that!

52
00:02:25,333 --> 00:02:27,533
That's the reason we'll put
this in the package.

53
00:02:27,600 --> 00:02:28,833
I have a plan.

54
00:02:29,900 --> 00:02:30,900
Why? Whose necklace is that?

55
00:02:32,333 --> 00:02:33,767
It's Amanda's.

56
00:02:34,267 --> 00:02:38,033
I got this from her when she
was like a crazy person.

57
00:02:39,067 --> 00:02:40,233
Oh, okay.

58
00:02:40,300 --> 00:02:41,867
So that's why you kept that.

59
00:02:41,933 --> 00:02:42,933
No.

60
00:02:43,000 --> 00:02:44,800
Do you think I kept
it for remembrance?

61
00:02:45,933 --> 00:02:48,200
I have a plan, Zandro.

62
00:02:49,600 --> 00:02:55,900
And I'm sure Eden will
hate her mom after this.

63
00:03:02,200 --> 00:03:03,733
Don't lose that.

64
00:03:08,100 --> 00:03:10,733
And you even made
those phone calls.

65
00:03:10,800 --> 00:03:13,000
My gosh, they're so convinced

66
00:03:13,067 --> 00:03:14,867
that Amanda was behind
all of it.

67
00:03:14,933 --> 00:03:18,200
I thought you'd accepted Eden

68
00:03:18,267 --> 00:03:19,567
now that she's due
to give birth.

69
00:03:20,067 --> 00:03:21,100
Of course, not.

70
00:03:21,200 --> 00:03:22,067
Never!

71
00:03:23,100 --> 00:03:25,833
I just don't want
Red to get hurt.

72
00:03:26,433 --> 00:03:28,967
That's why I'm putting
on an act.

73
00:03:29,033 --> 00:03:31,667
Rina, that baby is still
your family.

74
00:03:31,733 --> 00:03:35,367
Yes, but that baby has
Amanda's blood!

75
00:03:35,433 --> 00:03:39,367
Do you think I'll care
about that child?

76
00:03:39,433 --> 00:03:40,033
Never!

77
00:03:40,667 --> 00:03:42,500
Not even in my dreams.

78
00:03:43,067 --> 00:03:44,567
What are you going to
do when she gives birth?

79
00:03:44,633 --> 00:03:46,967
She'll give birth, yes.

80
00:03:47,033 --> 00:03:52,500
But they won't have a child to
bring home.

81
00:03:55,367 --> 00:03:57,767
I have a plan, Zandro.

82
00:03:58,500 --> 00:03:59,833
I have a plan.

83
00:04:02,100 --> 00:04:04,100
Why did you bring me here?

84
00:04:05,800 --> 00:04:06,967
You'll see.

85
00:04:19,267 --> 00:04:21,233
Did you think I wouldn't
find out?

86
00:04:22,100 --> 00:04:24,300
How long have you been cheating
me off of my money?

87
00:04:24,367 --> 00:04:26,667
You didn't turn in any
money three times.

88
00:04:26,733 --> 00:04:28,233
But it's just money.

89
00:04:29,400 --> 00:04:31,300
But you started poaching
my clients,

90
00:04:31,367 --> 00:04:33,333
and I can't let it slide.

91
00:04:33,400 --> 00:04:35,100
Forgive me, Lucho.

92
00:04:35,167 --> 00:04:36,433
I was desperate.

93
00:04:37,567 --> 00:04:39,733
Zandro is holding
my wife hostage.

94
00:04:40,600 --> 00:04:43,567
That's why I'm doing
everything he wants.

95
00:04:43,633 --> 00:04:45,800
You've been too greedy.

96
00:04:46,433 --> 00:04:48,200
You're a double-crosser!

97
00:04:48,500 --> 00:04:49,567
Sorry.

98
00:04:50,967 --> 00:04:53,167
Please, don't kill me.

99
00:04:53,233 --> 00:04:54,767
You won't die.

100
00:04:55,400 --> 00:05:00,433
But you'll get to taste hell.

101
00:05:09,333 --> 00:05:12,133
You double-crossed
the wrong person.

102
00:05:25,400 --> 00:05:26,300
Forgive me.

103
00:05:26,367 --> 00:05:28,900
- Please, don't kill me.
- I changed my mind.

104
00:05:47,467 --> 00:05:48,800
My dear child...

105
00:05:50,400 --> 00:05:53,733
A few more weeks and
I'll give birth to you.

106
00:05:55,267 --> 00:05:56,900
I'll get to see you.

107
00:06:06,333 --> 00:06:07,367
Who is it?

108
00:07:00,633 --> 00:07:01,367
Eden!

109
00:07:01,833 --> 00:07:02,867
What's going on?

110
00:07:05,600 --> 00:07:06,500
Auntie.

111
00:07:06,900 --> 00:07:07,633
Auntie.

112
00:07:08,933 --> 00:07:09,933
Oh my God!

113
00:07:10,400 --> 00:07:11,167
Oh my God!

114
00:07:11,867 --> 00:07:12,533
What is that?
A baby monster?

115
00:07:15,700 --> 00:07:16,667
Oh my God!

116
00:07:17,300 --> 00:07:19,033
Your water broke!

117
00:07:19,100 --> 00:07:21,000
You're about to
give birth, Eden!

118
00:07:21,533 --> 00:07:23,033
Zandro!

119
00:07:23,100 --> 00:07:23,900
Zandro, help!

120
00:07:24,500 --> 00:07:25,733
Zandro!

121
00:07:25,800 --> 00:07:27,300
Why? What's going on?

122
00:07:27,900 --> 00:07:29,733
Zandro, Eden is about
to give birth!

123
00:07:30,400 --> 00:07:32,000
Pick her up. Let's bring
her to the hospital.

124
00:07:35,300 --> 00:07:36,700
Hurry up, put her in the car.

125
00:07:56,300 --> 00:07:57,567
Sorry, Amanda.

126
00:08:00,400 --> 00:08:03,933
But you had to see what
happened earlier.

127
00:08:04,000 --> 00:08:05,200
To scare me off?

128
00:08:06,367 --> 00:08:07,633
Is that what you think?

129
00:08:15,933 --> 00:08:18,233
I just showed you my world.

130
00:08:18,500 --> 00:08:20,433
So you'll get to know me.

131
00:08:20,500 --> 00:08:23,800
And to make you aware of the
world you got yourself into.

132
00:08:24,267 --> 00:08:27,067
I don't care about your
illegal dealings.

133
00:08:27,133 --> 00:08:30,133
All I want is to get revenge.
I want to get my daughter back.

134
00:08:30,200 --> 00:08:32,000
You will get your revenge,
Amanda.

135
00:08:33,833 --> 00:08:35,233
As you heard earlier,

136
00:08:35,800 --> 00:08:38,067
Zandro's been messing
with my business.

137
00:08:39,633 --> 00:08:41,700
I will do it not because
you want to get revenge.

138
00:08:42,833 --> 00:08:44,000
I'll get mine too.

139
00:08:48,167 --> 00:08:50,467
Ouch! It hurts! I can't
bear the pain!

140
00:08:50,533 --> 00:08:52,400
We're almost there, Eden.
It won't take too long.

141
00:08:52,467 --> 00:08:53,967
Drive faster, Zandro!

142
00:08:54,033 --> 00:08:55,833
I'm driving as fast as I can!

143
00:08:55,933 --> 00:08:57,700
Call Red, please!

144
00:08:57,767 --> 00:08:58,767
I'll call him later.

145
00:08:58,833 --> 00:09:01,133
Just think about
your baby for now.

146
00:09:01,200 --> 00:09:02,400
Zandro, hurry up!

147
00:09:02,467 --> 00:09:03,633
I'm driving as fast as I can!

148
00:09:03,700 --> 00:09:07,167
- I can't get any faster!
- She's about to give birth!

149
00:09:08,300 --> 00:09:08,700
Hang in there!

150
00:09:08,767 --> 00:09:10,000
Hang in there!

151
00:09:10,067 --> 00:09:12,267
- We're almost there!
- It hurts!

152
00:09:12,900 --> 00:09:13,933
Rina, we have a problem.

153
00:09:14,000 --> 00:09:15,733
Problem? What problem?

154
00:09:15,800 --> 00:09:17,367
The car brake is not working!

155
00:09:17,433 --> 00:09:17,967
What?

156
00:09:19,933 --> 00:09:21,867
Do something about it, Zandro!

157
00:09:21,933 --> 00:09:22,933
Do something!

158
00:09:23,000 --> 00:09:24,700
I am!

159
00:09:24,767 --> 00:09:26,233
Hang in there, okay?

160
00:09:32,433 --> 00:09:34,900
I just want to make things
clear between us.

161
00:09:35,900 --> 00:09:40,033
I don't want blood in my hands.
No one is going to die, Lucho.

162
00:09:40,633 --> 00:09:42,833
I just want to get revenge.

163
00:09:42,900 --> 00:09:46,733
I just want them to feel
the way they made me feel.

164
00:09:52,800 --> 00:09:56,400
Eye for an eye,
tooth for a tooth.

165
00:09:57,200 --> 00:10:01,733
But are you sure that they
haven't killed you yet?

166
00:10:03,633 --> 00:10:07,367
You're not the same
Amanda they know.

167
00:10:08,900 --> 00:10:11,633
They killed that Amanda and
threw her in the garbage.

168
00:10:14,867 --> 00:10:17,233
You're a Mrs. Madrigal now.

169
00:10:18,567 --> 00:10:21,500
And no one can stop us.

170
00:10:33,867 --> 00:10:35,867
Wait, I feel dizzy.

171
00:10:36,233 --> 00:10:37,833
Oh my God, I feel dizzy.

172
00:10:39,100 --> 00:10:40,833
What the heck, Zandro!

173
00:10:41,600 --> 00:10:43,100
Is she okay?

174
00:10:43,633 --> 00:10:44,667
I don't know.
Eden?

175
00:10:45,233 --> 00:10:45,967
Eden.

176
00:10:46,867 --> 00:10:47,900
Eden, wake up.

177
00:10:49,800 --> 00:10:51,333
She lost consciousness.

178
00:10:52,900 --> 00:10:57,100
That's good, so we can
carry on with our plans.

179
00:11:33,800 --> 00:11:34,933
Be careful.

180
00:11:38,433 --> 00:11:39,333
- Thelma.
- Where are we?

181
00:11:40,200 --> 00:11:41,500
I'll take care of her.

182
00:11:44,033 --> 00:11:46,067
We didn't make it
to the hospital.

183
00:11:46,133 --> 00:11:49,100
But someone will help us.

184
00:11:49,167 --> 00:11:52,000
You need to get
the baby out.

185
00:11:52,867 --> 00:11:54,167
It hurts!

186
00:11:55,033 --> 00:11:56,300
Go on, push!

187
00:11:57,900 --> 00:11:58,667
Push!

188
00:11:58,733 --> 00:12:00,200
I can see the baby's head
already!

189
00:12:00,867 --> 00:12:01,400
Come on.
Come on, Eden. Push.

190
00:12:02,267 --> 00:12:03,267
You have to push.

191
00:12:03,767 --> 00:12:08,500
You have to get the baby out,
or it might die.

192
00:12:08,567 --> 00:12:09,367
Go on, push!

193
00:12:09,433 --> 00:12:10,933
You have to push, Eden.
Come on.

194
00:12:13,100 --> 00:12:14,833
There, it's almost there.

195
00:12:17,233 --> 00:12:20,300
Your baby's coming.

196
00:12:20,367 --> 00:12:21,167
One more push!

197
00:12:21,233 --> 00:12:23,167
- Push!
- Push! Come on!

198
00:12:25,300 --> 00:12:26,333
Very good!

199
00:12:26,400 --> 00:12:27,067
Yes.

200
00:12:41,433 --> 00:12:44,400
Forgive me, Eden, for
what I'm about to do.

201
00:12:45,500 --> 00:12:47,933
But I'm doing all
of this for you.

202
00:12:48,767 --> 00:12:52,800
To get you away from
the people you trust.

203
00:12:56,833 --> 00:12:58,700
I hope it's not too late.

204
00:13:20,067 --> 00:13:21,867
Where's my baby?

205
00:13:39,367 --> 00:13:43,267
Miss, is that my baby?

206
00:13:43,333 --> 00:13:44,900
You have a beautiful baby.

207
00:14:21,733 --> 00:14:23,600
Auntie, why are you crying?

208
00:14:27,900 --> 00:14:28,900
Eden...

209
00:14:30,133 --> 00:14:32,333
Auntie, what happened?

210
00:14:34,800 --> 00:14:36,667
Where's my baby, Auntie?

211
00:14:37,800 --> 00:14:39,767
Eden, your baby...

212
00:14:43,500 --> 00:14:44,900
your baby's gone.

213
00:14:46,533 --> 00:14:48,000
Your baby's gone.

214
00:14:48,933 --> 00:14:50,433
That's not true!

215
00:14:50,967 --> 00:14:52,167
- Your baby's gone.
- That's not true!

216
00:14:52,233 --> 00:14:53,767
- I heard my baby cry!
- Your baby's gone.

217
00:14:53,833 --> 00:14:55,533
- Where's my baby!
- It's gone!

218
00:14:55,600 --> 00:14:57,833
Your baby's gone!
It's gone!

219
00:14:58,567 --> 00:15:00,700
Where's my baby, Auntie?!

220
00:15:01,500 --> 00:15:03,000
The baby's gone, Eden.

221
00:15:05,333 --> 00:15:07,067
My baby's not gone.

222
00:15:07,133 --> 00:15:09,133
Where's my baby?

223
00:15:09,567 --> 00:15:11,700
Thelma did everything.

224
00:15:11,767 --> 00:15:12,467
Believe me.

225
00:15:12,533 --> 00:15:14,000
She did everything she could.

226
00:15:14,067 --> 00:15:15,667
She did everything.

227
00:15:15,733 --> 00:15:17,467
But when you lost
consciousness...

228
00:15:17,800 --> 00:15:21,033
your baby died.

229
00:15:21,500 --> 00:15:22,567
It's gone.

230
00:15:23,233 --> 00:15:24,300
The baby's gone.

231
00:15:24,967 --> 00:15:28,033
- That's not true!
- You have to be strong.

232
00:15:28,533 --> 00:15:30,833
You have to be strong, okay?

233
00:15:31,500 --> 00:15:33,000
Your baby's gone.

234
00:15:36,667 --> 00:15:38,800
My baby!

235
00:15:39,300 --> 00:15:40,200
- My baby!
- It's gone.

236
00:15:44,367 --> 00:15:45,900
My baby!

237
00:15:47,833 --> 00:15:50,133
Where is my baby, Auntie?

238
00:15:50,200 --> 00:15:52,000
Where is my baby?

239
00:15:58,633 --> 00:15:59,433
Hello, Mom.

240
00:16:00,267 --> 00:16:02,133
Yeah, I'm home.
Where are you?

241
00:16:02,200 --> 00:16:03,267
Red?

242
00:16:03,333 --> 00:16:04,533
Red, hurry.

243
00:16:04,800 --> 00:16:07,967
You have to come here to
St. Francis Hospital.

244
00:16:08,067 --> 00:16:09,700
Eden gave birth.

245
00:16:11,533 --> 00:16:12,367
Gave birth?

246
00:16:13,333 --> 00:16:14,067
How did that happen?

247
00:16:14,133 --> 00:16:15,200
She's not due to
give birth yet.

248
00:16:15,267 --> 00:16:17,200
She's only on her eight-month.

249
00:16:17,267 --> 00:16:19,867
I'll explain later.
Please, hurry!

250
00:16:19,933 --> 00:16:20,967
Hurry!

251
00:16:22,133 --> 00:16:23,733
Okay, I'll be on my way.

252
00:16:44,500 --> 00:16:47,433
Eden, have something to eat.

253
00:16:48,967 --> 00:16:50,600
I'm not hungry.

254
00:16:51,033 --> 00:16:53,833
I know, but you need to eat.

255
00:16:53,900 --> 00:16:55,400
You have to get
your strength back.

256
00:16:56,000 --> 00:16:56,800
Come on.

257
00:16:56,867 --> 00:16:59,167
Eat something,
even a little bit.

258
00:16:59,233 --> 00:17:00,000
Okay?

259
00:17:01,667 --> 00:17:03,800
Mom, Yen.

260
00:17:06,967 --> 00:17:07,900
What's happening?

261
00:17:08,700 --> 00:17:10,733
- Red...
- Why do you look like that?

262
00:17:13,833 --> 00:17:15,667
Can someone tell me
what's happening?

263
00:17:16,167 --> 00:17:17,600
How's our baby?

264
00:17:19,067 --> 00:17:20,167
The baby's gone, Red.

265
00:17:21,400 --> 00:17:23,000
He had left us.

266
00:17:27,800 --> 00:17:29,033
What do you mean he's gone?

267
00:17:31,800 --> 00:17:32,933
Red...

268
00:17:33,533 --> 00:17:38,333
your baby died soon after
Eden gave birth.

269
00:17:39,967 --> 00:17:41,633
We didn't make it
to the hospital.

270
00:17:41,700 --> 00:17:43,633
I'm sorry, Son.

271
00:17:58,933 --> 00:18:00,367
No.

272
00:18:03,667 --> 00:18:05,233
No.

273
00:18:07,100 --> 00:18:08,467
No.

274
00:18:11,900 --> 00:18:13,067
No.

275
00:18:17,233 --> 00:18:18,433
No!

276
00:18:18,500 --> 00:18:19,233
Red!

277
00:18:19,300 --> 00:18:20,867
- Red!
- No!

278
00:18:20,933 --> 00:18:23,500
Red!

279
00:18:23,600 --> 00:18:25,367
No!

280
00:18:28,467 --> 00:18:29,833
Son.

281
00:18:30,600 --> 00:18:31,867
Come here.

282
00:18:33,700 --> 00:18:38,000
No!

283
00:18:41,900 --> 00:18:43,967
Son.

284
00:19:02,200 --> 00:19:03,600
No!

285
00:19:10,200 --> 00:19:10,900
I know it hurts.

286
00:19:10,967 --> 00:19:11,967
I know that it hurts.

287
00:19:12,033 --> 00:19:17,067
Why do we have
to lose our baby?

288
00:19:17,133 --> 00:19:22,400
It's not your fault.

289
00:19:22,467 --> 00:19:23,633
Red.

290
00:19:23,700 --> 00:19:27,967
If no one scared Eden,
this wouldn't happen.

291
00:19:28,033 --> 00:19:30,033
This wouldn't happen.

292
00:19:34,100 --> 00:19:35,167
Who scared her?

293
00:19:35,233 --> 00:19:36,100
Who did it?

294
00:19:36,167 --> 00:19:37,500
Who scared her?

295
00:19:37,567 --> 00:19:40,867
Someone sent Eden
a dead fetus.

296
00:19:40,933 --> 00:19:44,900
She got so scared and
had premature labor.

297
00:19:44,967 --> 00:19:45,833
Dead fetus?

298
00:19:45,900 --> 00:19:48,500
What dead fetus?
Who sent it to her?

299
00:19:48,567 --> 00:19:50,000
It's Amanda.

300
00:19:50,067 --> 00:19:53,800
No one else but Amanda.

301
00:19:53,867 --> 00:19:56,533
It's all her fault.

302
00:19:56,600 --> 00:19:58,233
She killed your child.

303
00:19:58,300 --> 00:20:04,533
She killed her
own grandchild.

304
00:20:04,633 --> 00:20:07,533
I'm sorry, Red.

305
00:20:07,600 --> 00:20:09,267
I'm sorry.

306
00:20:13,867 --> 00:20:17,300
I don't know why my mom
wants to kill our baby.

307
00:20:17,367 --> 00:20:19,367
I'm sorry.

308
00:20:19,433 --> 00:20:21,500
I'm sorry.

309
00:20:48,933 --> 00:20:50,800
I'm sorry, Son.

310
00:21:25,000 --> 00:21:25,867
Zandro.

311
00:21:26,600 --> 00:21:27,633
How's it going?

312
00:21:28,467 --> 00:21:30,133
Don't worry, Rina.

313
00:21:30,700 --> 00:21:31,500
I'm taking care of it.

314
00:21:36,800 --> 00:21:37,933
Thank you.

315
00:21:39,433 --> 00:21:42,933
Just let me know if
that's not enough.

316
00:21:43,033 --> 00:21:44,100
I can give you more.

317
00:21:45,133 --> 00:21:46,933
You're a midwife, right?

318
00:21:48,833 --> 00:21:50,400
I need a fetus.

319
00:21:51,767 --> 00:21:52,467
Can you provide that?

320
00:21:53,567 --> 00:21:55,400
What are you going
to do with it?

321
00:21:57,767 --> 00:22:02,067
Let's just say I'm going
to give it as a gift.

322
00:22:03,467 --> 00:22:05,767
My son's fiancée.

323
00:22:07,000 --> 00:22:08,633
I can get that done.

324
00:22:09,233 --> 00:22:11,500
We can talk about it.

325
00:22:11,933 --> 00:22:15,567
You won't have a problem with me
if the price is right.

326
00:22:16,167 --> 00:22:17,633
That's what I like about you.

327
00:22:19,333 --> 00:22:21,633
I have more jobs for you to do.

328
00:22:23,500 --> 00:22:24,933
You'll make a lot of money.

329
00:22:26,033 --> 00:22:31,133
Just make sure I
can depend on you.

330
00:22:31,467 --> 00:22:33,033
No problem, Madam.

331
00:22:38,267 --> 00:22:40,800
So are you happy now?

332
00:22:40,867 --> 00:22:42,333
Things are running according
to your plans.

333
00:22:44,467 --> 00:22:49,867
Just make sure we won't
have a problem, Zandro.

334
00:22:52,267 --> 00:22:53,500
I don't want to fail.

335
00:22:59,267 --> 00:23:00,600
Thelma, Thelma.

336
00:23:01,700 --> 00:23:02,900
We're on our way there now.

337
00:23:14,067 --> 00:23:15,400
You know what to do.

338
00:23:16,033 --> 00:23:19,200
Yes, I'll switch it
with a dead baby.

339
00:23:20,100 --> 00:23:23,167
I don't want to see
that child ever again.

340
00:23:23,433 --> 00:23:25,500
Thelma, don't mess up.

341
00:23:25,567 --> 00:23:27,200
I don't want any problem.

342
00:23:27,333 --> 00:23:28,500
Don't worry.

343
00:23:28,567 --> 00:23:30,867
I know a lot of places where
I can sell this baby.

344
00:23:35,667 --> 00:23:37,533
I got rid of the baby.

345
00:23:38,033 --> 00:23:43,667
Now Red and Eden can break up.

346
00:23:55,533 --> 00:23:57,433
It's just a matter of time,
Rina.

347
00:23:57,500 --> 00:23:59,367
I'm getting ready to come back.

348
00:23:59,933 --> 00:24:04,767
You'll pay for everything
you did to me.

349
00:24:04,833 --> 00:24:07,833
If it's up to me,
the wedding is off.

350
00:24:07,900 --> 00:24:09,733
Well, that's good news, Auntie.

351
00:24:09,800 --> 00:24:11,400
It means that Red
is still single.

352
00:24:11,467 --> 00:24:15,133
Remember, a pretty face has
nothing against a flirty woman.

353
00:24:15,200 --> 00:24:16,233
I love Eden.

354
00:24:16,300 --> 00:24:19,333
But love is not enough
to get her back.

355
00:24:19,400 --> 00:24:21,233
I need to use force.

356
00:24:21,300 --> 00:24:22,500
All in one day?

357
00:24:22,567 --> 00:24:23,167
Everything is sold out?

358
00:24:23,233 --> 00:24:24,200
Yes, Ma'am.

359
00:24:24,267 --> 00:24:26,667
Only one person bought
all the bags you wanted.

360
00:24:26,733 --> 00:24:28,333
One person?

361
00:24:28,400 --> 00:24:29,400
Who is this person?

362
00:24:29,500 --> 00:24:31,333
It's Mrs. Madrigal.

363
00:24:31,400 --> 00:24:33,333
Mrs. Madrigal? Who?

364
00:24:33,400 --> 00:24:37,067
Meet my wife, Mrs. Madrigal.
